What the fuck?

I'll admit that I didn't know what to take away from this at first. Seemed like something that they could probably just contain with breaking a D-Class's fingers once a day and call it. So imagine my face when I read .

I really like this piece. The juxtaposition between the actions of the personnel, the reaction of the SCP, and the overall premise of  is just wild and I love it. I also appreciate that, while this is certainly a contender for the End of Death canon, that it doesn't really fit into it when everything is considered. This is its own separate universe, and it's clear from the interview log.

I do have my own thoughts as to what this piece could symbolize, but I think that would be projecting onto something that is just as satisfying being . This is an upvote from me.

